  "summary": "Chief Inspector Tsujimura and a group of investigators arrive at the Kyūgajō mansion to examine the crime scene in Itou's room. The room is a spacious, antique-furnished suite located at the end of a long, dim corridor. Upon entering, the investigators encounter Detective Horikawa, Detective Horiwell—a talented investigator and right-hand man to Saito Village—and Muto.\n\nThe investigators discover the body of Itou, an elderly man wearing a flashy blue woolen robe. The corpse is in a bizarre state: it is decapitated, with a bloody, dark cut where the head should be, and the feet have been severed. Muto explains the significance of the feet by demonstrating that the victim was wearing decorative medieval iron armor boots. Because such decorative armor is designed for aesthetic harmony rather than practical use, the boots are too small for human feet to fit inside; therefore, the feet had to be removed to put them on.\n\nThe identity of the victim is confirmed by a silver engagement ring on the right ring finger, which is embedded in the dry skin and engraved with the name \"Ito\" in Roman letters. While a housekeeper is expected to attest to the ring's ownership, the investigators note that the victim's head has not yet been found.",
